  "_comment_modem_sync": "Plan 002 B0.5/#197 software BPSK modem with channel impairments (fractional timing 0.4 + CFO 2e-4 cyc/sample + static phase ~33deg) and the full RX recovery chain (matched filter -> AGC -> M&M timing -> Costas phase -> Barker-13 frame sync/polarity -> slice), Barker-framed PRBS9 seed=1 snr=6dB 8000 payload bits. The recovery loops are sequential, so this runs symbol-by-symbol over a smaller frame than the bulk BER tiers and carries a much higher cyc/bit. Host model (identical fixed-point algorithm): frame locks @sym 20, recovered BER 2878 ppm vs theory 2388 (~1.2x, well inside the 4x ideal-sync bound). modem_sync_recover_snr6 cycles/ber_ppm are null until the first CI HIL capture populates them (same bootstrap as modem_shaped_*); the firmware asserts lock + the 4x BER bound + a coarse cyc/bit budget every run regardless. modem_sync_lock_sym is report-only (value = lock symbol index + 1).",
  "modem_sync_recover_snr6": { "ber_ppm": null, "cycles": null, "tolerance_percent": 20, "last_updated": "2026-06-30", "notes": "Report-only until seeded from the first CI HIL run; then runner-gated. Host model: BER ~2878 ppm vs theory 2388, lock @sym 20." },
  "modem_sync_lock_sym":     { "locked": null, "cycles": null, "tolerance_percent": 20, "last_updated": "2026-06-30", "notes": "Report-only: frame-lock symbol index + 1 (host model: lock @sym 20 -> value 21). Proves the Barker preamble was found." }
